### GL-01 Enterprise Setup — example requests
### Run `mvn spring-boot:run` first, then execute requests top-to-bottom with the REST Client
### VS Code extension — each response's id feeds the next request's variable.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@userId = prashanth

### 1. Create a consumption context (WORKSPACE)
# @name createContext
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/consumption-contexts
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "segmentType": "WORKSPACE",
  "code": "CTX-001",
  "name": "Coimbatore Manufacturing Group"
}

### Get consumption context by id
@contextId = {{createContext.response.body.data.id}}
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/consumption-contexts/{{contextId}}

### List all consumption contexts
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/consumption-contexts

### 2. Create a business group (THICK_ES — supports multiple Legal Entities)
# @name createBusinessGroup
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-groups
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "consumptionContextId": "{{contextId}}",
  "code": "BG-001",
  "name": "Coimbatore Manufacturing Group",
  "esMode": "THICK_ES",
  "defaultCurrency": "INR"
}

@businessGroupId = {{createBusinessGroup.response.body.data.id}}

### Get business group by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-groups/{{businessGroupId}}

### List business groups filtered by consumption context
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-groups?consumptionContextId={{contextId}}

### 3. Create a legal entity
# @name createLegalEntity
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/legal-entities
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "businessGroupId": "{{businessGroupId}}",
  "code": "LE-001",
  "name": "Coimbatore Plant Legal Entity",
  "accountingStandard": "IND_AS",
  "tan": "CHEE12345F"
}

@legalEntityId = {{createLegalEntity.response.body.data.id}}

### Get legal entity by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/legal-entities/{{legalEntityId}}

### List legal entities filtered by business group
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/legal-entities?businessGroupId={{businessGroupId}}

### Update legal entity (PATCH)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/legal-entities/{{legalEntityId}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "tan": "CHEE99999F"
}

### 4. Create a business unit (1 BU = 1 State = 1 GSTIN)
# @name createBusinessUnit
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-units
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "legalEntityId": "{{legalEntityId}}",
  "code": "BU-001",
  "name": "Coimbatore Plant",
  "gstin": "33AABCE1234F1Z5"
}

@businessUnitId = {{createBusinessUnit.response.body.data.id}}

### Get business unit by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-units/{{businessUnitId}}

### List business units filtered by legal entity
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-units?legalEntityId={{legalEntityId}}

### Update business unit (PATCH)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-units/{{businessUnitId}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "name": "Coimbatore Plant (Renamed)"
}

### 5. Create an inventory organisation (optional under Thin ES)
# @name createInventoryOrg
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/inventory-organisations
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "businessUnitId": "{{businessUnitId}}",
  "code": "IO-001",
  "name": "Main Warehouse"
}

@inventoryOrgId = {{createInventoryOrg.response.body.data.id}}

### Get inventory organisation by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/inventory-organisations/{{inventoryOrgId}}

### List inventory organisations filtered by business unit
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/inventory-organisations?businessUnitId={{businessUnitId}}

### 6. Create a sub-inventory
# @name createSubInventory
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/sub-inventories
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "inventoryOrganisationId": "{{inventoryOrgId}}",
  "code": "SI-001",
  "name": "Raw Materials Bin"
}

@subInventoryId = {{createSubInventory.response.body.data.id}}

### Get sub-inventory by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/sub-inventories/{{subInventoryId}}

### List sub-inventories filtered by inventory organisation
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/sub-inventories?inventoryOrganisationId={{inventoryOrgId}}

### 7. Audit log — every write above produced a CREATE entry
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/audit-log?entityName=legal_entity&entityId={{legalEntityId}}

### All audit log entries, most recent page
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/audit-log


### ── Rejection cases ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Thin ES: create a second Business Group with THIN_ES mode
# @name createThinBusinessGroup
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-groups
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "consumptionContextId": "{{contextId}}",
  "code": "BG-002",
  "name": "Chennai Trading Group",
  "esMode": "THIN_ES",
  "defaultCurrency": "INR"
}

@thinBusinessGroupId = {{createThinBusinessGroup.response.body.data.id}}

### First Legal Entity under Thin ES — succeeds (201)
# @name createFirstThinLe
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/legal-entities
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "businessGroupId": "{{thinBusinessGroupId}}",
  "code": "LE-THIN-001",
  "name": "Chennai Trading Legal Entity"
}

### Second Legal Entity under the same Thin ES group — rejected with 409 THIN_ES_LE_LIMIT
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/legal-entities
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "businessGroupId": "{{thinBusinessGroupId}}",
  "code": "LE-THIN-002",
  "name": "Second Legal Entity — should be rejected"
}

### Invalid GSTIN format — rejected with 400 INVALID_GSTIN
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-units
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "legalEntityId": "{{legalEntityId}}",
  "code": "BU-BAD-GSTIN",
  "name": "Invalid GSTIN Unit",
  "gstin": "NOT-A-VALID-GSTIN"
}

### Duplicate business group code within the same context — rejected with 409 DUPLICATE_CODE
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/business-groups
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "consumptionContextId": "{{contextId}}",
  "code": "BG-001",
  "name": "Duplicate Code Group",
  "esMode": "THICK_ES",
  "defaultCurrency": "INR"
}

### Unknown legal entity id — rejected with 404 RESOURCE_NOT_FOUND
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/gl/legal-entities/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
